<2ND_LINE>PM-Soldier's Rampage,0192</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Heartbroken Soldier Runs Amok, Kills Seven, Military Says</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MANILA, Philippines (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A soldier went berserk after a quarrel
with his girlfriend, firing a rifle at neighbors and villagers and
killing seven people, the military said today.
   The killer surrendered after the rampage, in which nine people
were injured, the military said.
   The report said Jesus Negro, a constable at the Special Action
Force, went on the killing spree after he left his girlfriend's home
Wednesday in Tiber, a village in Cebu province 360 miles southeast
of Manila.
   The military said the violence was triggered by a ``love
problem'' between Negro and the woman, who was not identified.
   After Negro left his girlfriend's home, he began firing his
semiautomatic rifle at neighbors in the coastal village. Five people
were killed and five others injured, the report said.
   Negro then hitched a ride in a jeep to nearby Talisay town. While
en route, he opened fire on a group of men in Lawaan village,
killing two and wounding four, the report added.
   He surrendered later and was undergoing interrogation, the report
said.
