<2ND_LINE>PM-China-Explosion,0182</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>45 Dead In Mine Explosion</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HONG KONG (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A gas explosion ripped through a coal mine in
northeast China, killing 45 workers and injuring 23, an official
Chinese report said today.
   The domestic China News Service, in a report appearing in the
Chinese-language New Evening Post newspaper, said the explosion
occurred Saturday afternoon in Jixi city, about 840 miles northeast
of Beijing.
   The report said the cause of the explosion was under
investigation and that top provincial officials went to the site to
help with the probe.
   No other details were provided in the brief report. The news
service did not say why the accident was not reported earlier.
   There have been several other fatal mine explosions in China this
year. More than 50 people died in a mine blast near Guiyang in
southern China's Guizhou province in May.
   A few weeks later, 49 people were killed in a coal mine explosion
in northern Shanxi province. In August, 44 miners died when a gas
explosion devastated a coal mine in western China's Gansu province.
</TEXT>
