<2ND_LINE>PM-Weatherpage Weather,0466</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Snow Dusts Northeast, Fog Hangs Through Northwest</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Light snow borne by colder northwest winds dusted areas from the
Great Lakes to the Northeast today and dense fog lingered throughout
much of the Northwest, cutting visibility in some spots to zero.
   In Michigan, snowfall was light with Flint and Lansing reporting
1 inch early today. Snow was also scattered across western parts of
the Pennsylvania, with snowfall amounts predicted in the 1 to 2 inch
range.
   In New York, rain and sleet fell on Buffalo, but the
precipitation was forecast to turn to snow. Snowfall amounts were
predicted to reach 6 inches south of Buffalo.
   Fog hovered early today in the California valleys through western
Oregon and over eastern Washington. Visibility was reduced to zero
at many locations, including the Sacramento area.
   Dense fog also was reported through eastern South Dakota,
reducing visibilities to 1 mile across the region.
   But fair skies were the rule across the rest of the nation early
this morning.
   Today's forecast called for snow through the central
Appalachians, much of Michigan and northern Maine; snowfall along
the shores of the lower Great Lakes; scattered showers through the
southern Florida peninsula; rain through much of Washington; and
fair skies through the central portion of the nation.
   High temperatures were forecast in the 20s in the upper Great
Lakes; in the 30s and 40s through the upper and middle Mississippi
Valley, the Ohio Valley, the Tennessee Valley, the Appalachians and
the northern and middle Atlantic coastal states; in the 30s and 40s
through the Pacific Northwest, the northern and central Rockies;
into the 70s through southern Florida peninsula and in the 70s and
80s over Southern California and southern Arizona; and in the 50s
and 60s throughout the rest of the nation.
   Temperatures around the nation at 2 a.m. EST ranged from 5
degrees below zero at International Falls, Minn., to 76 degrees at
the Naval Air Station at Key West, Fla.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 35 fair; Boston 44 cloudy; Charleston, S.C. 49
fair; Cincinnati 26 fair; Cleveland 33 cloudy; Detroit 32 snow;
Miami 71 partly cloudy; New York 45 cloudy; Philadelphia 42 partly
cloudy; Pittsburgh 32 cloudy; Portland, Maine 31 fair; Washington 42
fair.
   _Central: Bismarck 24 fair; Dallas-Fort Worth 40 fair; Denver 27
fair; Des Moines 20 fair; Indianapolis 25 fair; Kansas City 27 fair;
Minneapolis-St. Paul 09 fair; Nashville 33 fair; New Orleans 44
fair; St. Louis 35 fair.
   _West: Albuquerque 26 fair; Las Vegas 41 fair; Los Angeles 65
fair; Phoenix 52 fair; Salt Lake City 25 fair; San Diego 56 fair;
San Francisco 47 fair; Seattle 41 fair.
   _Canada: Montreal 37 partly cloudy; Toronto 34 partly cloudy.
</TEXT>
