<1ST_LINE>r a PM-BodiesFound     12-01 0327</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Bodies Found,0335</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>District Attorney Says More Bodies May Be Found</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DARTMOUTH, Mass. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The deaths of four women whose bodies
were discovered near highways are related and more bodies may be
found as a search of the area continues today, a district attorney
said.
   The bodies were discovered during the last five months, with the
latest found Tuesday.
   ``I feel pretty confident they are connected somehow. There may
be more than just the four women,'' Bristol County District Attorney
Ronald A. Pina said Wednesday.
   He said the body found Tuesday ``may be No. 5, not No. 4. There
may be another person out there is my concern, if not more.''
   Three of the bodies were discovered along Interstate 195 in this
southeastern Massachusetts town. The fourth was found along a state
road in nearby Freetown. Two of the bodies were discovered in July,
the other two in November. All four women were believed to have been
nude when killed, investigators said.
   Pina said it was possible that the four deaths were connected
with the deaths of two women from Providence, R.I., whose bodies
were found last spring off highways in southeastern Massachusetts.
   None of the four more recently found bodies has been identified.
   Pina said one person may have killed the three women whose bodies
were found here, and that the person was familiar with the area.
   ``The fact that they're all in the same area would lead you to
believe that a person has done more than one killing,'' he said.
``There's no doubt that those people were all murdered and left
there.''
   State Trooper William Delaney said the bodies were left in
similar locations within 15 feet of the tree lines off the highways.
But, he said, there also were dissimilarities in the cases.
   Four women have been listed as missing from nearby New Bedford in
the last several months, but no definite link between them and the
bodies has been made.
</TEXT>
