<HEAD>Museum Reopens as Guards Settle Strike with New Hours for Spring</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PARIS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An agreement was reached Thursday with security
guards at the Louvre to end a strike that closed the museum for 10
days, the Culture Ministry said.
   Strikers had protested a change in working hours due to the
opening of a new section of the museum next year.
