<1ST_LINE>d a AM-BRF--PlayingKlan     12-01 0156</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Playing Klan,0160</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Police Say Youngsters Were Playing Klan</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JACKSONVILLE, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   What was believed to be a gathering of
Ku Klux Klan followers over the Thanksgiving holiday was actually a
group of youngsters ``playing Klan,'' police say.
   Landowner Tom Alan told police he saw several truckloads of young
men leave a wooded area Saturday after he was confronted by a gunman.
   Police found a camp decorated with red swastikas and a large
banner reading ``Welcome Klansmen.''
   ``These guys were just playing. It got out of hand. It scared one
of the neighbors and it scared some of the participants,'' said
police Sgt. Steve Weintraub.
   He said police have identified eight people who were in the camp
but could not confirm that anyone had a gun.
   Although the area is posted with no-trespassing signs, it has
been a popular hangout for neighborhood youths for years. No one has
been charged with trespassing, Weintraub said.
</TEXT>
