<HEAD>Heflin Undergoes Minor Prostate Surgery</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Alabama Sen. Howell Heflin was in satisfactory
condition Thursday at Bethesda Naval Hospital after undergoing minor
prostate surgery the day before, Heflin's office said.
   A statement from Heflin's office said the 67-year-old senator was
resting comfortably with no complications after undergoing a
transurethral resection of the prostate. That is an operation
similar to the surgery President Reagan had in January 1987.
   Heflin's doctors found no evidence of cancer, the statement said,
and he was expected to be released from the hospital soon.
