source said NBC's bid was ``substantially higher'' than CBS'.
Olympic officials were seeking a minimum of $350 million.
   The Barcelona fee topped the previous record of $309 million paid
by ABC for the Winter Olympics in Calgary, Canada. The network lost
an estimated $75 million. NBC paid $300 million for the TV rights in
Seoul. Sources said NBC made a ``modest'' profit, but much lower
