<HEAD>Gannett Chairman Calls for Shultz to Resign</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Secretary of State George P. Shultz should
resign for his ``glandular reaction'' in denying a visa for PLO
Chairman Yasser Arafat to address the United Nations, Allen H.
Neuharth writes in a column in Friday's editions of USA Today.
   ``Drastic? Sure,'' wrote Neuharth, chairman of Gannett Co. Inc.
and founder of the newspaper. ``But better Shultz have egg on his
face as he rides off into the sunset than Uncle Sam have a black eye
for weeks or months.''
   Neuharth said Shultz should be replaced by James A. Baker III,
whom President-elect George Bush has picked to be his secretary of
state. Baker then should allow Arafat to address the U.N. General
Assembly in New York.
