Arafat on the ground the chairman of the Palestine Liberation
Organization supports terrorism.
   In his column, Neuharth wrote that the issue is not terrorism.
Instead, he said, ``It's simply whether the U.N. can invite anyone
it wishes to speak to it. How can the USA, champion of free speech,
be so presumptuous as to interfere?''
   Neuharth tempered his criticism with praise for Shultz's ``years
of faithful and often fruitful service'' with the federal government.
