<HEAD>US Concerned About Detention of Journalist in Honduras</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The State Department has expressed concern to
the Honduran government over the detention of Washington Post
correspondent Julia Preston, who was held incommunicado overnight
after arriving in Tegucigalpa, it was disclosed Thursday.
   ``We have requested an official explanation of these actions,''
State Department press officer Ben Justesen said.
