<2ND_LINE>PM-Chrysler Canada-Layoffs,0153</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Chrysler Laying Off more than 500 in Canada Due to Kenosha Closing</HEAD>
<DATELINE>AJAX, Ontario (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   About 530 workers at a Chrysler Canada trim
plant will lose their jobs beginning in January shortly after the
U.S. automaker closes its Kenosha, Wis., factory, a company
spokesman said today.
   ``This is a projection at this point, but that looks like the
number,'' said Walt McCall.
   Chrysler Corp., the No. 3 U.S. automaker and the parent company
of Chrysler Canada, has said it will close the plant in Kenosha on
Dec. 23 and lay off more than 5,000 workers.
   The trim plant in Ajax, just east of Toronto, employs about 2,000
people and makes interior components for many of Chrysler's North
American plants. The layoffs will be completed by July.
   ``No one likes to see this, but it's a cyclical business and it
happens,'' McCall said.
</TEXT>
