<HEAD>List of Biggest Corporate Acquisitions</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-RJR Nabisco Bjt</HEAD>
<TEXT>
   Here are the 10 biggest corporate acquisition deals in U.S.
history, including both mergers and leveraged buyouts. The list
gives the principal buyer, the value and the year completed for each
deal:
   _RJR Nabisco Inc., by Kohlberg Kravis Roberts & Co., $24.5
billion, pending.
   _Gulf Corp., by Chevron Corp., $13.4 billion, 1984.
   _Kraft Inc., by Philip Morris Cos. Inc., $12.6 billion, pending.
   _Getty Oil Co., by Texaco Inc., $10.1 billion, 1984.
   _Standard Oil Co., by British Petroleum PLC (which already owned
55 percent), $7.9 billion, 1987.
   _Conoco Inc., by DuPont Co., $7.4 billion, 1981.
   _Federated Deptartment Stores Inc., by Campeau Corp., $6.6
billion, 1988.
   _Marathon Oil Co., by USX Corp., $6.5 billion, 1982.
   _RCA Corp., by General Electric Co., $6.4 billion, 1986.
   _Beatrice Cos., by Kohlberg Kravis Roberts & Co., $6.1 billion,
1986.
