<TEXT>
   NBC won the U.S. television rights to the 1992
Summer Olympics in Barcelona, Spain, The Associated Press learned
today.
   NBC, which televised the Summer Olympics in Seoul, had been
considered a longshot to get the Barcelona rights. CBS was favored
because it already owns the TV rights to the 1992 Winter Games in
Albertville, France.
   The International Olympic Committee and the Barcelona Olympic
Organizing Committee scheduled a news conference later today for the
official announcement.
