<2ND_LINE>AM-Dollar-Gold,0433</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Dollar, Gold Mixed</HEAD>
<HEAD>Precede LONDON-BC</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By PETER COY</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>AP Business Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The dollar's value was little changed Thursday in
quiet trading that was uninfluenced by a U.S. government report
indicating sluggish economic growth.
   The Commerce Department said the Index of Leading Indicators
edged up a slight 0.1 percent in October. Analysts said the number
was within expectations.
   Also Thursday, the nation's largest general retailers said sales
continued at their now-familiar sluggish pace in November.
   Traders said the market was waiting for Friday's scheduled
release of U.S. unemployment figures for November. Market forecasts
anticipate the unemployment rate has stabilized at 5.3 percent.
   In Tokyo, the dollar fell 0.28 Japanese yen to a closing 121.57
yen. Later, in London, it slipped further to 121.40 yen. In New
York, the dollar fell to 121.43 yen from 121.48 late Wednesday.
   In London, the British pound rose to a six-month high of $1.8535
from $1.8480 late Wednesday. Later in New York, the pound also
traded at $1.8535, unchanged from late Wednesday.
   Other late dollar rates in New York, compared with late
Wednesday, included: 1.7296 West German marks, down from 1.7318;
1.4504 Swiss francs, up from 1.4498; 1.1868 Canadian dollars, up
from 1.1863; 5.9140 French francs, down from 5.9195; and 1,279.00
Italian lire, down from 1,279.50.
   Other late dollar rates in Europe, compared with late Wednesday,
included: 1.7300 West German marks, down from 1.7375; 1.4498 Swiss
francs, down from 1.4548; 5.9075 French francs, down from 5.9327;
1.9510 Dutch guilders, down from 1.9590; 1,278.00 Italian lire, down
from 1,284.97; 1.1855 Canadian dollars, down from 1.1872.
   Gold prices were mixed.
   In Hong Kong, gold bullion jumped $2.90 to close at a bid of
$425.52 a troy ounce.
   Gold was quoted in London at a late bid price of $423.25 a troy
ounce, unchanged from Wednesday's late bid price. In Zurich,
Switzerland, gold rose to a late bid of $424.90 an ounce, up from
$422.30 bid late Wednesday.
   On the Commodity Exchange in New York, gold bullion for current
delivery fell to $423.90 a troy ounce from $424.80 on Wednesday.
   Later, Republic National Bank of New York said gold was bid at
$422.85 a troy ounce as of 4 p.m. EST, down from $424.10 an ounce
late Wednesday.
   Silver bullion rose in London to a bid price of $6.15 a troy
ounce, up from $6.14 bid late Wednesday. On New York's Comex, silver
bullion for current delivery fell to $6.096 a troy ounce from $6.136
an ounce Wednesday.
</TEXT>
